            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 P.W./7–3045</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Swiss
                        Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grässli</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to the Chargé d’Affaires ad
                    interim of Switzerland in charge of Japanese interests in the United States with
                    the exception of the Territory of Hawaii and acknowledges the receipt of the
                    Legation’s note dated July 30, 1945 (Reference: I–10) transmitting the text of a
                    communication from the Japanese Government concerning alleged attacks by United
                    States <pb facs="0486" n="474" xml:id="pg_474"/> aircraft upon various Japanese
                    cities. It is noted that certain non-military objectives are said to have been
                    damaged during these attacks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-29">August 29,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
